THE WEEK AHEAD 
NAACP CONVENTION: Black leaders from throughout the United States will attend 
the NAACP's national convention beginning today at the Los Angeles Convention 
Center. 
Benjamin Hooks, the organization's executive director, will open the convention 
with a 7 p.m. speech. 
SKID ROW CAMP: The Fred Jordan Mission begins its third summer camp Monday, 
offering day activities for inner-city children at MacArthur, Ramona and 
Holenbeck parks. Camp activities are geared toward those aged 5 to 12. 
BLUE LINE: The Blue Line rail system that will link downtown Long Beach to 
downtown Los Angeles is to begin operations on Saturday. The trains will 
operate free of charge Saturday and Sunday with regularly scheduled service 
beginning July 16. 
